news.title: Nagpur's new development plan in offing, 90% of old plan still on paper after 25 years
news.para: Nagpur is nearing the deadline for its new Development Plan (DP), facing skepticism due to past failures. The city received 43 suggestions, mainly from landowners seeking removal of long-standing property reservations from the 2000 DP. With a December 2025 deadline, the NMC aims to create a comprehensive plan, but challenges remain in incorporating all areas and addressing unresolved reservations.

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha partners with Zepto to market housing plots
news.para: House of Abhinandan Lodha (HoABL) has partnered with Zepto to market its residential plots, starting with premium plots in Vrindavan and Neral. This collaboration expands HoABL's reach by allowing customers to discover and engage with their offerings on the Zepto app. Prospective customers can connect with an HOABL expert within 10 minutes for guidance via video call.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh forms panel to unlock land hurdles for industry
news.para: The Uttar Pradesh government has formed a high-level committee to optimize land utilization across Noida, Greater Noida, and Yamuna Expressway authorities. This decision addresses significant gaps between notified, master-planned, and acquired land, hindering industrial development. The committee will recommend strategies to accelerate land acquisition, streamline approvals, and unlock land parcels for industrial use, aligning with the state's investment promotion policy.

news.title: Rajasthan HC seeks details of plans for Jaipur's Walled City
news.para: The Rajasthan High Court has directed the state government to submit a comprehensive report detailing development plans and actions for Jaipur's Walled City. The court, emphasizing a broader scope beyond commercial activities, aims to address issues like waterlogging, parking, and traffic congestion within the historic area. The next hearing is scheduled for September 17.

news.title: Centre selects Chandigarh to implement ‘land stack’ project on pilot basis
news.para: Chandigarh has been chosen as one of the two locations in India for piloting the Land Stack project. A committee meeting was held to discuss its implementation. The project aims to create a transparent land records management system. It will provide a unified database for land details. This will streamline property transactions and urban planning.

news.title: Telangana CM to hand over keys to Indiramma beneficiaries on August 21
news.para: Chief Minister A Revanth Reddy will lead a ceremony on August 21 in Bendalampadu village, Bhadradri Kothagudem, to hand over keys to beneficiaries of the Indiramma housing scheme. Housing Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy highlighted the event's historical significance, noting that the CM will personally perform 'gruhapravesam' for 27 houses, marking the start of a project to build 4.

news.title: Telangana to roll out e-Aadhaar property registration, pilot project in two SROs
news.para: Telangana's registration and stamps department will introduce e-Aadhaar-based property registration soon. This aims to expedite services. The pilot project will launch in Armoor and Kusumanchi sub-registrar offices. The government has implemented reforms like slot booking. Integrated sub-registrar offices will be constructed across Telangana. A complex will be built in Gachibowli.

news.title: Bengaluru development body to launch 3D online platform for home purchase
news.para: ​​Except for final registration at the Sub-Registrar’s office, all other steps—from application and document submission to payments and ownership certificate—can be done online.

news.title: MPIDC plans revenue model for office spaces at IT Park 4 in Indore
news.para: MPIDC is developing a revenue model to offer office spaces to tech firms at the upcoming IT Park 4 in Indore. They've sought industry feedback to determine office space allocation across floors and anticipate bookings to begin by September. The Rs 42 crore project aims to attract over Rs 500 crore in investment and generate 4000 jobs.

news.title: NCLT declares ex-DHFL chairman bankrupt over ₹4,546 crore dues
news.para: The NCLT Mumbai has declared Kapil Wadhawan, the former chairman of DHFL, bankrupt following a petition by Union Bank of India to recover ₹4,546 crore. This order was issued after Wadhawan failed to submit a repayment plan. Sanjay Kumar Mishra has been appointed as bankruptcy trustee to manage the distribution of Wadhawan's estate.

news.title: About 3,000 bighas to cement company in sixth schedule area shocks Gauhati HC
news.para: Gauhati High Court expressed strong disapproval over the allocation of 3,000 bighas of land to a cement company in Assam's Dima Hasao district, a region protected under the 6th Schedule of the Constitution. The court questioned the decision, emphasizing the need to prioritize the rights and interests of the tribal people and considering the area's environmental significance.

news.title: Mohali development body earns ₹961 crore from e-auction of properties
news.para: Gmada's recent e-auction generated Rs 961 crore, fueled by strong commercial mixed-use site sales in Aerocity and intense bidding for SCOs and shops in Sector 78. While residential plot prices saw a slight dip compared to June, overall earnings surged. However, certain categories like petrol pumps and hotel sites saw no interest, indicating cautious investor sentiment.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB to gauge demand for sector 54 housing project, conduct a survey soon
news.para: The Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) is set to conduct a survey to assess demand for its proposed housing project in Sector 54, with tentative apartment prices being calculated. The project will include EWS flats and accommodate approximately 1,700 units on 32 acres.

news.title: Solve super-built puzzle on flat cost information: Credai to West Bengal government
news.para: Credai West Bengal has appealed to the state's chief secretary regarding a recent amendment requiring super built-up area (SBUA) details for stamp duty assessment. This new rule has disrupted sale deed registrations, causing confusion due to the lack of a standardized SBUA definition.

news.title: Flat owners’ association urges KSPCB to allow temporary use of common sewage facilities in Kochi
news.para: Kerala flat owners' association (COFVOAK) has requested the state pollution control board (KSPCB) to permit apartment complexes without sewage treatment plants (STPs) to utilize common treatment facilities temporarily.

news.title: MahaRERA suspends 4,812 lapsed projects, freezes bank accounts
news.para: MahaRERA has suspended registrations of 4,812 housing projects across Maharashtra due to developers' failure to update construction progress or seek extensions. These projects, concentrated in urban areas like Pune and Thane, face transaction bans and penalties. The move aims to enforce transparency and protect homebuyers' interests by ensuring project accountability and completion.

news.title: Greater Noida authority allows buyers’ association to finish Sampada Livia project
news.para: Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority supports the Sampada Livia housing project. The project faced decade-long delays. GNIDA approved map extensions and mortgage permissions. This allows buyers to get loans. The project is under official supervision. Construction restarted in January 2023. Two towers reached the 23rd floor. The association plans to deliver flats by 2026.

news.title: Over 560 booked a month for dumping construction debris in public spaces in Nagpur
news.para: Nagpur grapples with rampant illegal dumping of construction materials, obstructing footpaths and roads. The NMC's Nuisance Detection Squad penalizes hundreds monthly, collecting substantial fines, yet the problem persists. Political interference hinders enforcement, leaving residents inconvenienced as public spaces remain encroached upon by debris, causing congestion and safety concerns.

news.title: NBCC expects revenue to double by FY28 at around ₹25,000 crore
news.para: State-owned NBCC Limited anticipates significant revenue growth. The company projects revenue of approximately twenty-five thousand crore rupees by fiscal year 2028. This is more than double the previous year's figures. The company's order book stands at one point two lakh crore rupees. NBCC expects the order book to exceed two lakh crore rupees soon.

news.title: Country Garden wins bank creditor group's support for offshore debt overhaul
news.para: Country Garden, grappling with a significant debt crisis after defaulting on $11 billion in offshore bonds, has secured an agreement with a core group of bank creditors holding 49% of its offshore debt. This marks progress in its $14.1 billion restructuring plan, aiming to reduce its offshore debt burden by 78%.
